modules.description: This module supports associative map operations over integer keys using little-endian Patricia trees, enabling efficient insertion, deletion, and lookup alongside transformations like mapping, filtering, and merging. It works with polymorphic value types and emphasizes key-based traversal and predicate-driven queries without relying on key ordering, making it suitable for sparse integer indexing or dynamic data aggregation where order independence is critical. Use cases include managing hierarchical data, sparse arrays, or scenarios requiring functional transformations over large integer-keyed datasets.
